const notes = [
  {
    key: 1,
    title: "Delegations",
    content:
      "Event Delegation is basically a pattern to handle events efficiently. Instead of adding an event listener to each and every similar element, we can add an event listener to a parent element and call an event on a particular target using the . target property of the event object",
  },
  {
    key: 2,
    title: "Loops",
    content:
      "Loops are used in JavaScript to perform repeated tasks based on a condition. Conditions typically return true or false . A loop will continue running until the defined condition returns false",
  },
  {
    key: 3,
    title: "Arrays",
    content:
      "Arrays are a special type of objects. The typeof operator in JavaScript returns object for arrays. But, JavaScript arrays are best described as arrays. Arrays use numbers to access its elements",
  },
  {
    key: 4,
    title: "JSON",
    content:
      "JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation JSON is a text format for storing and transporting data JSON is self-describing and easy to understand",
  },
];
